value: The Role of Bone Allografts in the Treatment of Angular Malunions of the Distal Radius

comment: The study compared two groups retrospectively
Fracture type inferred based on malunited extra-articular fracture.
Dorsal angulation mentioned as an exclusion criteria.
Gap is described by "shortening on the anteroposterior plane" in mm.
Volar locking plate explicitly mentioned as the operative technique.

value: This study found that bone allograft did not improve the final outcome for distal radius angular malunions when volar cortical contact was maintained using a volar locked plate.
